# .cursorrules

You are an expert TypeScript/React/Next.js developer.

## Code Style
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use `const` arrow functions for components
- Always add proper TypeScript types
- Use descriptive variable and function names

## Patterns
- Use React Query for data fetching
- Use Zustand for client state management
- Use Server Actions for mutations (`use server`)
- Use Zod for validation
- Follow existing patterns in codebase

## Testing
- Write tests with Vitest
- Use Testing Library for component tests
- Mock external dependencies
- Test edge cases and error conditions

## Don't
- Don't use `any` type
- Don't use class components
- Don't use inline styles (use Tailwind CSS)
- Don't create files over 200 lines
- Don't hardcode values

## Architecture
- Keep components small and focused
- Use custom hooks for shared logic
- Separate business logic from UI components
- Use proper error boundaries

## Performance
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Implement proper loading states
- Optimize re-renders
- Use proper key props in lists

## Security
- Validate all user input
- Use proper authentication patterns
- Don't expose sensitive data
- Follow OWASP guidelines